896595 12 Power to appoint Advisory Committee.
382416 1The Central Government may for the purpose of advising it on all matters of policy connected with the constitution and administration of the Corps appoint a Central Advisory Committee consisting of the following persons, namely:-
217449 athe Minister for Defence, who shall be the Chairman of the Committee;
748654 bthe Secretary to the Government of India, Ministry of Defence, ex- officio;
1911086 cthe Secretary to the Government of India, Ministry of Education, ex- officio;
639285 dthe Financial Adviser, Defence, ex- officio;
344289 e1 the Chief of the Army Staff, ex- officio;
918764 fthe Chief of the Naval Staff, ex- officio;
1606107 gthe Chief of the Air Staff, ex- officio;]
439680 hfive non- official members to be nominated by the Central Government; and
905747 i2 three Members of Parliament of whom two shall be elected by the House of the People and one by the Council of States.]
579442 1A3 A member elected under clause (i) of sub- section (1) shall hold office for a period of one year from the date of his election or until he ceases to be a Member of the House which elected him. whichever is earlier.]
1994845 2The Central Government may also appoint for the same purpose as is specified in sub- section (1), such 4 State Advisory Committees as it may consider desirable from time to time and may prescribe their duties and functions.
1503302 13 Power to make rules.
882965 1The Central Government may make rules 5 to carry out the objects of this Act.
644287 2In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power such rules may-
1538684 aprescribe the conditions subject to which universities of schools shall be allowed to raise units under this Act
